      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/49/5",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ اِشْتَرَى عَبْداً وَ لَهُ أَوْلاَدٌ مِنِ اِمْرَأَةٍ حُرَّةٍ فَأَعْتَقَهُ قَالَ \"وَلاَءُ أَوْلاَدِهِ لِمَنْ أَعْتَقَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3498 - Safwan ibn Yahya narrated from Al-Is ibn Al-Qasim, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as), about a man who purchased a slave that had children from a free woman, and then the man freed the slave.\nImam (as) said: \"The wala' (bond of loyalty) of his children belongs to the one who freed him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
